If there's no binding on an array rest pattern, is the binding code still required to exhaust the iteration? 

ie. 

```js

let generated = 0;
function* counting_generator() {
    generated = 0;
    for (var i = 0; i < 10; i++) {
        generated++;
        yield i;
    }
}

match (counting_generator()) {
    when [a,b,...]: {
        console.log(generated); // This prints... 3? 10?
    }
}
```
